    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Ambassador</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the French Republic</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: It appears from a telegram
                    that I have just received from my government that the Sultan of Morocco has
                    adopted the draft of programme which the Government of the Republic and the
                    German Government had agreed to propose to him, and assents to the conference
                    that is to take up the Moroccan affairs meeting at Algeciras.</p>
                <p>By order of my government I have the honor to bring this intelligence to your
                    excellency’s knowledge. I further append hereto, with reference to the
                    conversation I had with you previously on the subject, <pb facs="0795" n="675"
                        xml:id="pg_675"/> the text of the protocol concerning the project under
                    consideration, which was signed on September 28 by M. Rouvier and Prince
                        Radolin.<note n="a" xml:id="d684fna">The inclosure is word for word the same
                        as the memorandum printed on <ref target="#pg_673">p. 673</ref>, handed to
                        the Secretary by the French ambassador on October 3, and as the inclosure
                        with the German embassy’s note of the same date as this.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
